  "texts": [
    "Let EKG old = (V old, E old, R old, A old) represent the current state of the EKG, where: where ∆(O) represents the changes induced by the observations.",
    "The update process includes:• Adding new entities (e.g., detected objects):V new = V old ∪ {v new },where v new represents a newly detected object.",
    "• Updating attributes (e.g., object positions, temperatures):A new = A old ∪ {(v i, a j, d j)},where v i is an entity, a j is an attribute, and d j is the updated value.• Adding or modifying relationships (e.g., spatial relationships):E new = E old ∪ {(v i, r j, v k)},where v i and v k are entities, and r j is a relationship type.",
    "4) Graph Attention Networks (GATs) for Prioritization:To prioritize critical nodes and edges during task plan validation, we employ Graph Attention Networks (GATs).",
    "GATs compute attention weights α ij for nodes i and j in the Embodied Knowledge Graph (EKG), enabling the robot to focus on the most relevant aspects of the environment."
